						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab in the village.</p>						

						<p>Undated. Written in Telugu characters of 15th-16th century A.D. (?).</p>						

						<p>The inscription is fragmentary and seems to record the campaigns of some king (name lost) and refers to the consecration of a Śiva temple, and to the setting up of a pillar of victory. Mentions Narasiṁha • • • • • [pā?]truḍu, the <hi rend="italic">ūḷigam</hi> of the Mahārāja and to the gifts made by the former for the <hi rend="italic">Vasantotsava</hi> of Ahōbalēśvara. It could be an inscription of the Gajapatis of Cuttack, because they were assisted by officers/generals whose names have the suffix <hi rend="italic">Pātruḍu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
